; =======================================
; FIRST LAYER ADHESION TEST
; Ender 3 - Glass Bed - PLA
; =======================================
; Nozzle: 210°C (slightly hot for better adhesion)
; Bed: 60°C
; First layer height: 0.2mm
; Line width: 0.4mm (standard 0.4mm nozzle)
; Speed: 20 mm/s (slow for adhesion test)
; 
; Prints 5 squares in different bed regions
; so you can check adhesion across the bed.
; Watch it print - lines should be flat and
; slightly overlapping, not round spaghetti.
; =======================================

; --- STARTUP ---
G90                     ; Absolute positioning
M82                     ; Absolute extruder
G28                     ; Home all axes
M104 S210              ; Set nozzle to 210°C
M140 S60               ; Set bed to 60°C (no wait - preheat from LCD first!)
M109 S210              ; Wait for nozzle temp only
G92 E0                 ; Reset extruder
G1 Z5 F3000            ; Lift nozzle

; --- PRIME LINE (left edge) ---
G1 X2 Y20 F3000        ; Move to prime start
G1 Z0.2 F1000          ; Lower to first layer height
G1 X2 Y180 E15 F600    ; Prime line
G1 X2.4 Y180 F3000     ; Shift over
G1 X2.4 Y20 E30 F600   ; Second prime line
G92 E0                 ; Reset extruder

; =======================================
; SQUARE 1 - CENTER (110, 110)
; 40mm x 40mm filled square
; =======================================
G1 Z1 F1000
G1 X90 Y90 F3000
G1 Z0.2 F1000

